title: Engineering Analysis I
desc: Introduction to linear algebra from computational, mathematical, and applications viewpoints. Computational methods using a higher-level software package such as MATLAB.

title: Engineering Analysis  II
desc:
Linear algebra and introduction to vector methods in engineering analysis. Statics and dynamics of rigid bodies and matrix analysis of trusses and networks. Engineering design problems. 
Prerequisites: C- or better in GEN_ENG 205-1; MATH 220-1.

title: Engineering Analysis III
desc:
Dynamic behavior of the elements. Modeling of mechanical (both translational and rotational), electrical, thermal, hydraulic, and chemical systems composed of those elements. 
Prerequisite: C- or better in GEN_ENG 205-2.

title: Engineering Analysis IV
desc:
Solution methods for ordinary differential equations, including exact, numerical, and qualitative methods. Applications and modeling principles; solution techniques. 
Prerequisites: C- or better in GEN_ENG 205-2; MATH 220-2.

title: Mentored Study Program
desc: Study sessions facilitated by undergraduate peer leaders, for students enrolled in GEN_ENG 205-1. Meets weekly in small groups to collaboratively review material, solve practice problems, clarify concepts, and enhance study strategies. Enrollment optional. Graded S/U.

desc: Fulltime registration in an academic program in the continental United States that is affiliated with Northwestern. Upon successful completion of the program, registration is replaced with credits transferred from the affiliated institution.
